        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "pipeline: normalized provider→channel stream grammar (core)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nNormalizes every provider wire format into **one** event grammar — final text, thinking/reasoning, narration/commentary, tool activity, usage, errors — under **emit always, archive always, gate only at presentation**. This is the **core half** of a stacked pair; the Discord presentation gate follows on top (see below).\n\nDesign narrative + full normative spec, evidence captures, and a 35-test conformance harness:\n- RFC: openclaw/rfcs#16 — https://github.com/openclaw/rfcs/pull/16\n- Spec repo: https://github.com/Marvinthebored/openclaw-provider-stream-spec\n\nExtends the agent event I/O contract (`docs/channels/agent-event-io-contract.md`, #92216); four points are marked **[AMENDS BASE]** in the spec.\n\n## What's in this PR (core only)\n\n- Adapters **emit always**: wire-carried reasoning is no longer dropped at the source (`streamReasoning && onReasoningStream` gate and the `emitReasoning` discard removed as *emission* gates; `onReasoningStream` survives as a channel render hook).\n- Normalized `thinking` (raw/summary/redacted, dual-lane dedup), `assistant` commentary/final phases, tool `start`-at-earliest, lifecycle terminal + synthetic `stream_closed`.\n- Finality resolution: durable final **replaces** the draft segment (no dedup heuristics); zero-text finalize emits no final; Reject is a destructive settle.\n- Dispatch gates reasoning/narration at presentation; gateway mirrors thinking on its own stream + archives the normalized sequence.\n- Catalog: kimi-k2.6/k2.5 marked as reasoning models.\n\n## Scope / stacking\n\n- **Core, dispatch, catalog only.** No channel rendering here.\n- Discord presentation gate is stacked on this branch: `Marvinthebored:pipeline-discord` (Marvinthebored/openclaw#2; its isolated diff is Discord-only). It requires this PR to run.\n- Each branch is independently checkout-able so contributors can patch and test ahead of landing.\n\n## Status / testing\n\n- ⚠️ **Draft.** Built off a ~2-day-old merge-base; expect a \"behind main\" notice and possible rebase before merge (≈29 of our files overlap recent upstream churn in this hot area).\n- `tsgo:core` ✓ and `tsgo:extensions` ✓ — **the core branch typechecks standalone against the *unmodified* Discord plugin** (changes are backward-compatible).\n- Full vitest suite not yet run on the split branch (pre-PR suite gate pending).\n- History squashed for the draft; per-commit history available on `pipeline-rebase`.\n\n## Unresolved\n\n- **deepseek** reasoning/text boundary: deepseek (no clean reasoning-end signal) can fold its final answer into the thinking block; boundary fix in progress, follow-up commit on this branch.\n- The four [AMENDS BASE] points must also land in `agent-event-io-contract.md` (sequencing with #92216).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
